  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Transoesophageal ultrasound examination before and after prone position.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      Patients undergoing spinal surgery in the prone position are anaesthetized and then an
      ultrasound probe is placed in the oesophagus and the heart physiology is examined. Following
      prone position the examination is repeated.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
